snippet: Voters chose Dr. Vázquez, who served as president from 2005-10, over Luis Lacalle Pou, whose conservative National Party had vowed to scale back the legalization of marijuana.
abstract: Uruguayan voters elect Tabare Vazquez as president; victory highlights support for leftist coalition that has governed country over past decade, presiding over robust economic growth and pioneering set of socially liberal laws.

byline.original: By SIMON ROMERO and MAURICIO RABUFFETTI
byline.contributor: Simon Romero reported from Rio de Janeiro, and Mauricio Rabuffetti from Montevideo, Uruguay.

lead_paragraph: Voters chose Dr. Vázquez, who served as president from 2005-10, over Luis Lacalle Pou, whose conservative National Party had vowed to scale back the legalization of marijuana.

headline.main: Tabaré Vázquez Reclaims Presidency in Uruguay Election
headline.print_headline: Leftist Reclaims Presidency in Uruguay Election
